<v ->When I finished ‘The Field,’ which required that I</v>

22
00:00:57.445 --> 00:01:00.980
talk to quantum physicists all around the planet

23
00:01:00.981 --> 00:01:03.983
to try to understand why things like spiritual healing

24
00:01:03.985 --> 00:01:07.286
work and homeopathy work, I put together

25
00:01:07.288 --> 00:01:11.691
all of their work into a synthesis that suggested

26
00:01:11.693 --> 00:01:16.693
that consciousness is a living thing, an actual energy,

27
00:01:16.698 --> 00:01:18.865
with the ability to change physical matter.

28
00:01:18.866 --> 00:01:22.801
And this is the unfinished business I was left with

29
00:01:22.803 --> 00:01:24.436
after finishing that book.

30
00:01:24.438 --> 00:01:26.873
I wanted to know, being the kind of

31
00:01:26.875 --> 00:01:30.643
practical person that I am, fact-based person I am,

32
00:01:30.645 --> 00:01:33.513
how far can you go with this?

33
00:01:33.515 --> 00:01:35.381
What can you do with intention?

34
00:01:35.383 --> 00:01:37.850
You know, can I help my children pass their math tests

35
00:01:37.851 --> 00:01:39.051
with my thoughts?

36
00:01:39.053 --> 00:01:42.155
And more importantly, can I use my thoughts

37
00:01:42.156 --> 00:01:44.890
to do something to alleviate the vast catalogue

38
00:01:44.891 --> 00:01:46.793
of suffering on the planet?

39
00:01:46.795 --> 00:01:49.295
So I wanted to find out about this,

40
00:01:49.296 --> 00:01:51.130
and I also wanted to know about the mechanism

41
00:01:51.131 --> 00:01:52.998
by which intention works.

42
00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:56.403
You know, what science out there could explain this to me?

43
00:01:57.205 --> 00:01:59.905
So I went back to scientists,

44
00:01:59.906 --> 00:02:03.075
and I also wanted to find out about group thought.

45
00:02:03.076 --> 00:02:05.578
You know, does this magnify when lots of people

46
00:02:05.580 --> 00:02:08.481
are thinking the same thought at the same time?

47
00:02:08.483 --> 00:02:10.583
But the science that I came up with

48
00:02:10.585 --> 00:02:14.853
on that regard was very tantalizing, but inconclusive.

49
00:02:14.855 --> 00:02:17.323
So I was mulling this over one night with my husband

50
00:02:17.325 --> 00:02:18.625
and he turned to me and he said,

51
00:02:18.626 --> 00:02:21.560
“Why don’t you do these experiments yourself?”

52
00:02:21.561 --> 00:02:24.096
And I thought, ‘That sounds really ridiculous,’

53
00:02:24.098 --> 00:02:26.098
because you know, I’m not a physicist,

54
00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:28.501
I’m not any kind of a scientist.

55
00:02:28.503 --> 00:02:30.870
But as I started to think about it

56
00:02:30.871 --> 00:02:32.971
I thought, ‘Well, one thing I do have

57
00:02:32.973 --> 00:02:35.908
‘is a lot of participants in the form of my readers.

58
00:02:35.910 --> 00:02:38.378
‘I’ve got readers all over the globe.

59
00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:42.081
‘So perhaps if invite them to be part of this experiment

60
00:02:42.083 --> 00:02:44.583
‘we’ll have the largest mind-over-matter experiment

61
00:02:44.585 --> 00:02:45.851
‘in history.’

62
00:02:45.853 --> 00:02:48.321
And so that’s what I decided to do:

63
00:02:48.323 --> 00:02:49.788
make it a living book,

64
00:02:49.790 --> 00:02:52.291
so that the book doesn’t really have an ending.

65
00:02:52.293 --> 00:02:54.693
It is all about the science of intention,

66
00:02:54.695 --> 00:02:57.263
and what makes you a master of intention,

67
00:02:57.265 --> 00:02:59.798
and what kind of practical techniques you can use,

68
00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:02.068
but it’s also an invitation for readers

69
00:03:02.070 --> 00:03:04.970
to come on periodically, come on our website,

70
00:03:04.971 --> 00:03:09.971
and work with me working with scientists around the globe

71
00:03:10.145 --> 00:03:13.145
sending intention to particular targets.

72
00:03:13.146 --> 00:03:16.381
And our targets are all philanthropic,

73
00:03:16.383 --> 00:03:18.818
they all have a philanthropic implication.

