00:29:24.816 --> 00:29:28.820
let’s go back to your experiment

671
00:29:28.821 --> 00:29:30.256
and where you started going after the plants.

672
00:29:31.390 --> 00:29:33.825
<v ->Okay, in terms of studying?</v>

673
00:29:33.826 --> 00:29:35.826
<v Regina>Yes.</v>
<v ->Well, I wanted to look</v>

674
00:29:35.828 --> 00:29:38.630
at other things like negative intention,

675
00:29:38.631 --> 00:29:41.700
because many people ask me,

676
00:29:41.701 --> 00:29:43.701
“Oh, positive intention must be more powerful

677
00:29:43.703 --> 00:29:45.070
“than negative intention.”

678
00:29:45.071 --> 00:29:46.536
And so I wondered about that.

679
00:29:46.538 --> 00:29:49.706
You know, are thought to harm more powerful

680
00:29:49.708 --> 00:29:51.208
than our thoughts to heal?

681
00:29:51.210 --> 00:29:55.680
And sadly, negative intention,

682
00:29:55.681 --> 00:29:57.481
from data that I’ve seen,

683
00:29:57.483 --> 00:30:00.218
is every bit as powerful as positive intention.

684
00:30:00.220 --> 00:30:02.420
There’ve been many studies of

685
00:30:02.421 --> 00:30:05.356
people asked to kill something.

686
00:30:05.358 --> 00:30:07.391
Now of course studies in a lab

687
00:30:07.393 --> 00:30:11.095
don’t allow us to kill any kind of creature,

688
00:30:11.096 --> 00:30:13.263
much less a human being,

689
00:30:13.265 --> 00:30:15.800
so they’ve had to do them on micro-organisms,

690
00:30:15.801 --> 00:30:17.935
and they’ve found, they’ve done all kinds of studies

691
00:30:17.936 --> 00:30:21.305
on things like e coli bacteria, showing that when

692
00:30:21.306 --> 00:30:24.175
someone sends an intention to increase it,

693
00:30:24.176 --> 00:30:26.911
so a positive intention, that works.

694
00:30:26.913 --> 00:30:28.880
When someone tells them to send,

695
00:30:28.881 --> 00:30:32.116
when someone’s asked to send a negative intention,

696
00:30:32.118 --> 00:30:34.485
to kill it, that works too.

697
00:30:34.486 --> 00:30:36.586
And of course that’s the kind of thing that we use

698
00:30:36.588 --> 00:30:38.723
all the time.

699
00:30:38.725 --> 00:30:41.358
Many patients, with cancer for instance,

700
00:30:41.360 --> 00:30:44.261
told to visualize will send an intention

701
00:30:44.263 --> 00:30:45.696
to kill the cancer.

702
00:30:45.698 --> 00:30:46.831
Or if they have an infection

703
00:30:46.833 --> 00:30:49.433
to kill the micro-organism,

704
00:30:49.435 --> 00:30:51.101
to kill the infection.

705
00:30:51.103 --> 00:30:54.038
So that was really intriguing to me,

706
00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:56.875
and I wondered how do you protect yourself?

707
00:30:56.876 --> 00:30:58.743
I was really concerned about that.

708
00:30:58.745 --> 00:31:01.145
And there’ve been a couple of studies

709
00:31:01.146 --> 00:31:03.881
examining just that, where they’ve asked people

710
00:31:03.883 --> 00:31:07.451
to maintain a mental block against intention.

711
00:31:07.453 --> 00:31:10.221
Um, where somebody is sending an intention

712
00:31:10.223 --> 00:31:12.523
to them, and they’re supposed to form a psychic bubble

713
00:31:12.525 --> 00:31:13.691
of some sort.

714
00:31:13.693 --> 00:31:16.695
And some of them work and some of them don’t.

715
00:31:16.696 --> 00:31:19.596
So I thought to myself, ‘Well, that’s not very

716
00:31:19.598 --> 00:31:21.598
‘conclusive, and it’s also not a very good thing

717
00:31:21.600 --> 00:31:22.833
‘to do, I don’t think.’

718
00:31:22.835 --> 00:31:25.470
To walk around sort of self-enclosed

719
00:31:25.471 --> 00:31:27.505
in a psychic bubble, sort of separating yourself

720
00:31:27.506 --> 00:31:29.706
even more from the world.

721
00:31:29.708 --> 00:31:33.611
So I started pondering this, and I was very interested

722
00:31:33.613 --> 00:31:36.380
in the work of Dr. John Diamond, who wrote

723
00:31:36.381 --> 00:31:38.483
‘Your Body Doesn’t Lie,’

724
00:31:38.485 --> 00:31:41.886
and had really developed more than anyone else,

725
00:31:41.888 --> 00:31:43.655
earlier than anyone else, the whole concept of

726
00:31:43.656 --> 00:31:45.823
behavioral kinesiology.

727
00:31:45.825 --> 00:31:49.126
Using kinesiology, the muscle testing,

728
00:31:49.128 --> 00:31:51.428
to determine whether somebody is effected

729
00:31:51.430 --> 00:31:53.163
by toxic thoughts.

730
00:31:53.165 --> 00:31:56.366
And Dr. Diamond has a wonderful idea

731
00:31:56.368 --> 00:31:57.868
he calls “the homing thought.”

732
00:31:57.870 --> 00:32:02.840
Which is having someone maintain and keep

733
00:32:02.841 --> 00:32:06.778
aware of the thought that they were put on this earth

734
00:32:06.780 --> 00:32:10.381
to do, the activity that brings them in touch with

735
00:32:10.383 --> 00:32:11.315
the divine.

736
00:32:11.316 --> 00:32:13.751
He calls “cantillation” and and I think this is

737
00:32:13.753 --> 00:32:16.386
absolutely brilliant because he’s done many

738
00:32:16.388 --> 00:32:18.623
thousands of tests on subjects when they

739
00:32:18.625 --> 00:32:20.791
kept that “homing thought” as he calls it

740
00:32:20.793 --> 00:32:25.730
in place, and he’s found that that seems

741
00:32:25.731 --> 00:32:28.466
to guard and protect against negativity

742
00:32:28.468 --> 00:32:29.333
more than anything.

743
00:32:29.335 --> 00:32:31.368
Their arms, when they keep their homing thought

744
00:32:31.370 --> 00:32:33.671
strong, stays strong.
<v Regina>That makes sense.</v>

745
00:32:33.673 --> 00:32:36.808
When you’re connected with the essential

746
00:32:36.810 --> 00:32:38.241
nature of your being.

747
00:32:38.243 --> 00:32:39.276
<v ->Yes, exactly.</v>

748
00:32:39.278 --> 00:32:41.880
<v Regina>Don’t diffuse yourself or lose yourself.</v>

749
00:32:41.881 --> 00:32:43.246
<v ->Exactly.</v>

750
00:32:43.248 --> 00:32:45.350
<v Regina>Let’s talk about negative self-chat,</v>

751
00:32:45.351 --> 00:32:46.885
which isn’t exactly intention,

752
00:32:46.886 --> 00:32:49.520
but which people participate in

753
00:32:49.521 --> 00:32:52.423
sometimes a good percentage of their waking hours.

754
00:32:52.425 --> 00:32:55.326
<v ->Well you know, I think it does become intention.</v>

755
00:32:55.328 --> 00:32:57.561
I think that’s a really good question because

756
00:32:57.563 --> 00:32:59.996
you know, people think intention has to be this kind of

757
00:32:59.998 --> 00:33:03.400
mental oomph where you’re just projecting your awareness

758
00:33:03.401 --> 00:33:08.401
and really, really efforting to make that thing happen.

759
00:33:08.841 --> 00:33:12.610
And I’m not so sure this is the case after studying this,

760
00:33:12.611 --> 00:33:16.080
because it’s clear that we’re sending out

761
00:33:16.081 --> 00:33:20.016
transmissions all the time with our light emissions.

762
00:33:20.018 --> 00:33:23.453
And it’s clear that a thought is part of that transfer.

763
00:33:23.455 --> 00:33:26.690
So if all of this is clear, most of us are beaming out

764
00:33:26.691 --> 00:33:29.160
negative information most of the time.

765
00:33:29.161 --> 00:33:31.161
All of that negative chat, as you say,

766
00:33:31.163 --> 00:33:34.365
is there like a running commentary.

767
00:33:34.366 --> 00:33:37.201
‘How did you muff that today?’

768
00:33:37.203 --> 00:33:39.703
And that kind of thing, that just negative

769
00:33:39.705 --> 00:33:42.373
self-critical stuff and that judgmental stuff

770
00:33:42.375 --> 00:33:45.008
about other people, and that I think

771
00:33:45.010 --> 00:33:47.278
after a while becomes your intention.

772
00:33:47.280 --> 00:33:49.846
I think that becomes your life’s intention

773
00:33:49.848 --> 00:33:52.383
if you aren’t careful about it.

774
00:33:52.385 --> 00:33:55.453
<v Regina>That’s a very interesting take on it.</v>

